            <title>[PIG-1984] Nedd to clarify unknown schema</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PIG-1984</link>
                <project id="12310730" key="PIG">Pig</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;We need to clarify how unknown schema is used in Pig. For every field, if user don&apos;t tell us the data type, we use bytearray to denote an unknown type. In the case when we don&apos;t even know how many fields, Pig will derive unknown (null) schema.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;For example:&lt;br/&gt;
a = load &apos;1.txt&apos; as (a0, b0);&lt;br/&gt;
a: &lt;/p&gt;
{a0: bytearray,b0: bytearray}

&lt;p&gt;a = load &apos;1.txt&apos;;&lt;br/&gt;
a: Schema for a unknown&lt;/p&gt;</description>
